Package com.orientechnologies.orient.core.sql.parser

Class AggregateProjectionSplit

java.lang.Object
com.orientechnologies.orient.core.sql.parser.AggregateProjectionSplit
public class AggregateProjectionSplit extends Object
This class is used by the query planner to split projections in three parts:
  • pre-aggregate projections
  • aggregate projections
  • post-aggregate projections
An example: select max(a + b) + (max(b + c * 2) + 1 + 2) * 3 as foo, max(d) + max(e), f from " + className will become a + b AS _$$$OALIAS$$_1, b + c * 2 AS _$$$OALIAS$$_3, d AS _$$$OALIAS$$_5, e AS _$$$OALIAS$$_7, f max(_$$$OALIAS$$_1) AS _$$$OALIAS$$_0, max(_$$$OALIAS$$_3) AS _$$$OALIAS$$_2, max(_$$$OALIAS$$_5) AS _$$$OALIAS$$_4, max(_$$$OALIAS$$_7) AS _$$$OALIAS$$_6, f _$$$OALIAS$$_0 + (_$$$OALIAS$$_2 + 1 + 2) * 3 AS `foo`, _$$$OALIAS$$_4 + _$$$OALIAS$$_6 AS `max(d) + max(e)`, f
Author:
Luigi Dell'Aquila (l.dellaquila-(at)-orientdb.com)
